,Recommended,297370,20153882,"Posted: 31 December, 2015",all,paulo.ferraz.oliveira,"What's the game about?Sperm... erm... a fish ""swims"" around in a strange world, finding ""food"", finding other ""fishes"" to interact with (and sometimes they follow you to help you), ""fighting"" off ""bad fishes"", collecting orbs and finding light inside walls as well as gaining ""powers"" like the Red, the Green and the Grey. There's lots of color and space for metaphors regarding light vs. darkness, black on white, and stuff.General feeling after finishing?Very minimalistic setting that works well. I especially enjoying all the swimming and rescuing friends as well as discovering the levels. The game is quiet, but well paced, has no indication of ""damage"" (even when ""fighting"") and tells a story without words. The content of the story is, of course, open to interpretation, and uh... you SHOULD play it!Story?It can mean a lot of different things, so experiencing it is the best way to figure out what it's about.Gameplay?Works well with a PS3 controller and you mostly spend your time ""swimming"" and eating stuff, growing and shrinking when ""attacked"".Graphics?It's gorgeous, and the level design is mostly superb.Sound & Music?Sound design seems simple (that's probably its strength) but well adapted to the game. The music has that spacey feeling most of the time and I especially enjoyed the joyful parts where the music is very uplifting. It's mostly orchestrated music even if written in a machine (I don't know).Replayability?I guess it has some, yes..."
