76561198203401576,Not Recommended,297370,20736632,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,silverwolfdemon,"It's a beautiful game, no doubt, and I've played similar but this one just doesn't resonate with me.I find it to be more tedious and frustrating than actually relaxing. Going through the game, you want to keep your white fish with you, but they get caught on all manner of things or just fall behind. As a result, I find myself going back trying to get them out repeatedly. Perhaps you are supposed to leave them there, but that leaves you vulnerable to the black fish and makes you feel kind of like a a-hole (it's hero of many, not deserter of many).I also find the noise the black fish make to be quite irritating (it's a shrill monkey-like noise).The puzzles provided in the game are easy and far between. As a result, most of what you'll be doing is accidentally losing your fish as you go through a tunnel. Or accidentally trapping yourself by rolling a rock you thought you needed to move into the only exit, efficiently blocking it and forcing you to start over.On the plus side, check points are frequent, the music is nice (but not outstanding), and the game looks good."
