,Recommended,297370,14870230,"Posted: 13 March, 2015",all,Shadrach,"Hero of Many is a wonderful and original little indie game, with lovely art and music , set in a world where forces of light and dark are in constant battle.  The gameplay is pretty simple, and while you do get some new abilities, it's mostly about guiding and taking care of your little group and make sure that they don't take on too many enemies at a a time.Unfortunately, the gameplay does get repetitive after a while, and it's not really interesting enough to support the 7 or so hours the game takes. Several times I thought a cutscene meant the end, only to be put in a very similar level only with different background color. At the end I was just rushing through, not exploring, having lost the patience. If you want to invest the time for an at times very lovely and meditative experience, it's well worth it , even though it gets long-winded.In conclusion,  a wonderful little game - but outstays it's welcome a bit by being simply too long for the very basic game play."
